Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with model-checking for first- and monadic second-order logic on ordered structures. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses classes of structures with bounded treewidth and bounded expansion. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper considers the tractability and intractability of the model-checking problem. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with finite relational structures and posets. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as model-checking is a fundamental problem in automated reasoning and verification, which are important topics in AI.
